                    <row>
                        <cell>SUBJECT: </cell>
                        <cell cols="2">Orientation </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>


                <p>An orientation session for new Board Members was held on Thursday, <date
                        value="2001-04-05">April 5, 2001</date>, in the Lower West Oval Room of the
                    Rotunda. New Members <name type="present">Thomas F. Farrell, II</name> and <name
                        type="present">Thomas A. Saunders, III</name>, attended, as well as <name
                        type="present">Ms. Sasha L. Wilson</name>, the new Student Member. The
                    Rector, <name type="present">John P. Ackerly, III</name>, presided. The
                    President, <name type="present">John T. Casteen, III; Leonard W.
                        Sandridge</name>, Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer;
                        <name type="present">Peter W. Low</name>, Vice President and Provost; <name
                        type="present">Robert W. Cantrell, M.D.</name>, Vice President for Health
                    System; <name type="present">Paul J. Forch</name>, General Counsel; and <name
                        type="present">Alexander G. Gilliam, Jr.</name>, Secretary to the Board,
                    participated.</p>

                <p>The orientation, which was held in Open Session, began at 2:30 p.m. and concluded
                    at 4:00 p.m. It was conducted along the following lines:</p>
                <list>
                    <item>1. Overall view of the Board, its Committee structure and its workings
                            (<name type="person">Mr. Ackerly</name>).</item>
                </list>
                <pb n="2"/>
                <p>Orientation              &mdash;       <date value="2001-04-05">April 5, 2001</date>        &mdash;          2.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>2. The Organization Table of the University: How the University works and
                        who the players are (<name type="person">Mr. Casteen</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                    <item>3. An overview of the University’s Budget (<name type="person">Mr.
                            Sandridge</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                    <item>4. The University and State Appropriations (<name type="person">Mr.
                            Casteen</name> and <name type="person">Mr. Sandridge</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                    <item>5. The University’s overall rankings in comparison with its peers; the
                        determining factors and the Board’s role (<name type="person">Mr.
                            Casteen</name> with comments by <name type="person">Mr. Low</name> and
                            <name type="person">Dr. Cantrell</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                    <item>6. The workings of the Board in the context of the Virginia Freedom of
                        Information Act (<name type="person">Mr. Forch</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                    <item>7. A brief miscellany of Board housekeeping matters (<name type="person"
                            >Mr. Gilliam</name>).</item>
                    <lb/>
                </list>
            </div1>
